wikipedia_page.main: Frank Collier (26 April 1933 – 1 September 1989) was an English professional rugby league footballer who played in the 1950s and 1960s. He played at representative level for Great Britain, and at club level for Wigan (Heritage № 535), Widnes and Salford, as a fullback, prop and second-row, i.e. number 1, 8 or 10, or, 11 or 12, during the era of contested scrums.
